### CATEGORY D — FORWARD DEPENDENCIES AND ORDERING ERRORS
*These will cause tasks to fail because they reference systems built later.*

**D1 — TASK-083 references HP before HP exists**
TASK-083 (Phase 8) applies HP damage from Jing depletion. HP is defined in TASK-120 (Phase 14). Phase 8 runs before Phase 14. The simulation tick will try to modify a field that doesn't exist for 6 phases.

**D2 — TASK-119 (enemy node targeting) before TASK-121 (node damage)**
TASK-119 describes enemies cracking nodes. TASK-121 defines what cracking means. They are in the same phase (Phase 13/14) but wrong order. TASK-119 must call functions defined in TASK-121 and should be numbered after it.

**D3 — TASK-100 is UI work inside a logic phase**
TASK-100 (Phase 11) says "add to upgrade requirements UI a Reverse Meridians Available section." Phase 11 is progression logic. This task belongs in Phase 28 or 29 (UI phases).

**D4 — Jing depletion in Phase 8 references maxBodyHeat from Phase 7**
TASK-083 references total Jing capacity as "total Jing capacity across all nodes." But T2 capacity is scaled by FlowBonus (Phase 5) and qualityMultiplier (Phase 1). The "total Jing capacity" is not a simple sum — it requires computing per-type soft caps (TASK-082) which is also Phase 8. The ordering within Phase 8 matters and is not specified.

