### CATEGORY E — UNDERSPECIFIED MECHANICS
*These will cause the implementing agent to make arbitrary decisions that conflict with the GDD.*

**E1 — No enemy encounter trigger system**
TASK-113 initializes combat from `startCombat(state, enemy)`. Nothing defines HOW the player encounters an enemy. Is there a world map? Random encounters during cultivation? Manual "Enter Combat" from a zone list? No task creates the encounter trigger. Without it, combat cannot be entered.

**E2 — Formation Arrays require a "rest location" that doesn't exist**
TASK-130 says Formation Arrays are placed at "player's rest location." No task in the entire list defines a rest location, a home base, a world system, or any location-based infrastructure. Formation Arrays cannot be implemented without this.

**E3 — DaoComprehensionChallenge event never created**
TASK-099 says Sahasrara rank advancement requires a "DaoComprehensionChallenge event (flag set by special combat/event)." Neither Phase 12 (Dao) nor Phase 13 (Combat) includes a task that creates or fires this event. The Rank 9 cap for Sahasrara is permanently blocked as written.

**E4 — Companion body initialization undefined (TASK-158/159)**
The companion has `cultivation (GameState subset — own T2 nodes and meridians)`. What is a "GameState subset"? Does the companion have all 24 T2 nodes? A fixed subset? The same Dao? The same topology? The companion body is never initialized, making TASK-159 (companion simulation) impossible to implement.

**E5 — Active repair Jing routing to shattered nodes (TASK-124/125)**
TASK-124 computes repair progress from "jingInNode/node.capacity." A shattered T2 node is LOCKED and treated as inactive — its T1 nodes are set to UNSEALED (TASK-123). UNSEALED T1 nodes with all weights at zero (because edges were last set for routing away from the node) will have no Jing flowing in. No task describes how Jing reaches the shattered node's T1 cluster for repair.

**E6 — IO node default weights when receiving (TASK-028 et al.)**
Each topology defines default weights for outgoing edges. But IO_BIDIR nodes sometimes act as IO_IN (receiving from a meridian). The energy that arrives at the IO_IN T1 node must then be routed inward by the player's weight settings — but what weights? The default weights on edges FROM the IO node (outward into the cluster) are defined. What is the initial weight on those edges for a new, freshly-receiving IO_IN node? This is never stated. The player may have set weights for export (IO_OUT mode) that are wrong for distribution (IO_IN mode).

**E7 — TASK-102 and TASK-103 contradict each other**
TASK-102 says it creates "Dao node topologies" but ends by describing "each Dao has 5–7 Dao nodes with their own T1 cluster topologies." TASK-103 says "define skills for each Dao" but TASK-102 also mentions skills. The boundary between what 102 and 103 implement is ambiguous. Additionally, 8 Daos × 5–7 Dao nodes = 40–56 new T1 cluster topologies to design — buried as a single task. This is a massive underestimate.

**E8 — Tribulation pausing cultivation mid-heat (TASK-146)**
"Cultivation pauses" during a tribulation. But heat dissipation (TASK-070) is part of the simulation tick. If the tick is paused, heat stops dissipating. If the player entered tribulation while running Yang Qi, their heat level freezes during the fight, then heat resumes post-tribulation at whatever level it was, possibly triggering immediate node damage. No task addresses heat state during tribulation pause.

**E9 — Calendar "once per in-game day" mechanism unspecified (TASK-155)**
"Add advanceCalendar called from tick (once per in-game day)." One in-game day = 720 real seconds = 7,200 ticks. No task specifies how the tick function knows it's been 7,200 ticks (a modulo check on tick counter), or whether advancing by fast-forward multiplier accelerates the calendar. Unspecified.

**E10 — Sect selection trigger missing (TASK-137–140)**
Dao selection has an explicit trigger event (TASK-104). Sect selection has no equivalent. TASK-140 says "player can join one Sect (irreversible)" but no task creates the selection UI, trigger condition, or the moment it is presented to the player.

**E11 — Multiple saved circulation routes not supported**
GameState has `activeRoute: CirculationRoute | null` — one route at a time. No task adds a route library (saved named routes the player can swap between). Late-game players who use different routes for different goals (Shen accumulation, Yang Qi training, pre-combat heating) have no way to save their configurations.

